  abstract = {Advance pricing agreements (APAs) determine transfer prices for intra-Örm transactions in advance of tax Öling. This paper presents a model in which these contracts serve to overcome a hold-up problem that occurs because governments cannot commit to non-excessive future tax rates. We Önd that implemented APAs lead to a Pareto improvement even when all agents are risk neutral. Multilateral APAs are, in general, more e¢ cient than unilateral ones. However, not all e¢ cient APAs are concluded in equilibrium, due to asymmetric information problems. For the same reason, equilibrium APAs are highly complex, just as in practice. Surprisingly, APAs may lead to an increase in proÖt shifting to the low-tax location and, in most cases, do not allow for a reduction in audit capacity.},
